Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, crack the @egg{1} into a #bowl{} and whisk.

In another large bowl, combine the @breadcrumbs{50%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @oil{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs.

Drain the @monkfish medallions{200%g}, then pat dry with #kitchen paper{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}.

Dip the monkfish into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish and discard any excess egg.

Transfer the monkfish to a lined baking tray. Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the monkfish is cooked through and the crumb is crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The monkfish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the bottom 2cm from the @asparagus{100%g} and discard. Cut the asparagus in half widthways.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @chives{1%bunch} (use scissors if easier).

Heat a drizzle of oil in #medium saucepan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add half the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir through the @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated) and half the chives, then remove from the heat. Season with @pepper{}.

About ~{7-8%minutes} before everything's ready, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the asparagus and @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until they have softened and are lightly charred, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Next, add the @peas{120%g} and remaining garlic. Stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat. Cover to keep warm.

Once everything's ready, share the monkfish between your #plates{}. Serve the roast potatoes and veg alongside.

Reheat the chive sauce if needed (add a splash of water if it has become a little thick) and spoon it over the monkfish.

Sprinkle the remaining chives over everything to finish.

Enjoy!